$interpreted: Soohyeon: Tindoiimu…
Tindoiimu: I have nothing to say to you.
Tindoiimu: Let’s just get this over with.
Soohyeon: I won’t lose here!
Soohyeon: I must protect everyone!
Bull Soldier: Arbiter Maeok, we have an emergency situation!
Maeok: Shush! We’re in the middle of the tournament!
Bull Soldier: Y-Yes, I apologize, but I’ve been ordered by our general to report to you immediately.
Maeok: Why? Has something happened to the Bull Chieftain? To the tribe!?
Bull Chieftain: Yes, I’m afraid so!
Turtle Chieftain: Arbiter, we all know the bulls may be impetuous, but they don’t cry wolf!
Qing-Feng: If they say something important, then it really must be important. Maybe you should hear them out.
Maeok: Ah… Very well, what is it?
Bull Soldier: Our army discovered something at Pearl Manor…
Bull Soldier: Li Hwa, of the Jellyfish Tribe, is colluding with humans from the Kingdom of the Sun and… harboring bewitchers! There are dozens of them!
Soohyeon: What…!?
Maeok: Li Hwa… Kingdom of the Sun… harboring bewitchers…!?
Unsettled Audience: Dozens of them!? You must be joking!
Shun: Arbiter Marok, this cannot be excused! We must send out forces immediately!
Maeok: Yes, but, we can’t be too hasty…
Qing-Feng: And yet we all know how dangerous those bewitchers are. This may not be a time where slow and steady wins the race!
Maeok: And yes this brings the Kingdom of the Sun into the picture…
Qing-Feng: What’s more important!? The safety of the Alliance, or foreign ties!?
Maeok: Carry out my orders… Detain any and all Kingdom of the Sun citizens currently residing within the Alliance!
Maeok: The Alliance Army will set out for Pearl Manor at once!
Alliance Soldier: Yes, Arbiter!
Soohyeon: H-How could we be found out?
Toyokuni: …But, didn’t the maiden of Pearl Manor travel abroad? There should be nobody there right now…
Tindoiimu: ……
Soohyeon: ……I am absolutely disappointed, disgusted by my own home.
Soohyeon: Not only by what they’ve done to the Insect Tribe, but by what they’ve done to people like me… forced us into hiding…
Soohyeon: …Wait, could it be…!?
Soohyeon: …Was it… you? Tindoiimu?
: I’m sorry.
Soohyeon: It’s… It’s all my fault!
Chiyuki: Soohyeon, if you leave like this, you’ll forfeit the tournament!
Soohyeon: Mother! Take back those orders! They… they…
Soohyeon: They’re hiding out there in hope! In hope they can find a cure!
Maeok: Quiet! Enough with your nonsense!
Soohyeon: But, mother… They’re people, too! They’re part of this alliance, with just as much of a right to live as anybody else!
Soohyeon: And as our arbiter, you should protect them, not─
Maeok: Shut up!!
Juan-Yun: Maeok…?
Maeok: You listen to me!
Maeok: As arbiter, it is my job to take into account the safety of my people!
Maeok: And the day those people become bewitchers was the day they stopped being citizens of this alliance!
Soohyeon: …No longer… citizens…
Soohyeon: Then… what about me?
Maeok: What are you talking about? You’re my daugh─
Soohyeon: Who am I…
Juan-Yun: Soohyeon…?
Yonghyeon: It can’t be…
Maeok: Sooh… yeon…!?
Scared Audience: Is a bewitcher!?
Soohyeon: So, mom? What am I…?
Maeok: Soohyeon…
Soohyeon: Don’t look away─look at me!
Maeok: Soohyeon…
Soohyeon: Look at me! I’m one of them!
Maeok: But, Soohyeon… why…
Soohyeon: I’m… a bewitcher.
Yonghyeon: It can't be, Soohyeon…
Qing-Feng: Kong Soohyeon! You're from such a prestigious family, you've learned the way of the sage... and now you're a bewitcher!? What a waste!
Qing-Feng: Now, colluding with the enemy... you insolent, disloyal little girl! Come, apprehend her!
Juan-Yun: Hold on, father, that’s Soohyeon!
Qing-Feng: Shut up, you have no right to speak.
Qing-Feng: You are to be tried for treason, a serious crime! You will remain locked up until your trial!
Maeok: Wait…
Turtle Chieftain: Everything Qing-Feng said is…
Maeok: Wait… but…
Seahorse Chieftain: Soohyeon knows the law, and she’s broken it! Just look at her, that’s proof enough! Get her!
Maeok: No…
Toyokuni: Arbiter.
Toyokuni: Everyone is watching.
Yonghyeon: So, who has the guts to do it!?
Yonghyeon: Toyokuni! You!
Toyokuni: Enough, Yonghyeon! She’s a bewitcher, you know what must be done, you can’t protect her.
Yonghyeon: But… she’s a contestant! She holds the holy talisman!
Qing-Feng: She gave that up the moment she left the arena! She’s not a contestant anymore, she’s just a criminal!
Yonghyeon: Oh, shut up, old man!
Toyokuni: Enough! We’ll lock her up, first, then have a trial. It’s the only way.
Toyokuni: We need to stop all this torture, for her, and for the rest of them.
Yonghyeon: Yaaagh~~~!!!
Soohyeon: Tindoiimu, why!? Why did you have to do this!?
Tindoiimu: ……
Soohyeon: I know the Alliance has hurt you, but… but they’re innocent!!
Soohyeon: And you’re a good person, I know you’re a good person…
Soohyeon: Why… you’ve become just like them…
Tindoiimu: ……
Yao: What do you need from me?
Dracontine: Something’s going on at the tournament.
Yao: What is it?
Dracontine: …With something like this happening, I fear the tournament will be put on hold.
Yao: There’s no way that could happen.
Yao: Those people hold The Way of the Sage with more importance than anything else.
Yao: And now, everything is falling into place. We’re at the final stage.
Yao: Tell him, it’s time.
Dracontine: But…
Yao: No buts.
Yao: This is my battle, now.
Juan-Yun: Butter…?
Juan-Yun: Tindoiimu… is it you…?
Tindoiimu: ...Hehehe...
Juan-Yun: What’s happening to you? Why have you done this to yourself?
Tindoiimu: *Whimpers*
Tindoiimu: Because… I want revenge.
Tindoiimu: I want to kill you all.
Tindoiimu: I want to kill you all…
